[3] India (Mumbai)
Date: 13 Oct 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Indo-Asian News Service 10 Oct 2003 [edited]
<http://www.hindustantimes.com/news/181_411341,000600010004.htm>

160 cases of dengue reported in Mumbai
----------------------------------------------
Health authorities in Mumbai have reported 160 cases of dengue, with 2
fatalities, in the past 2 months. Of these cases, 8 are in a critical
condition in hospitals across the city, officials said.
The 2 victims who succumbed to the disease lived in upmarket areas of the
city. One was from posh Pali in suburban Mumbai. The other victim was the
teenaged son of a well-known doctor in Bandra. Both had contracted the
worst form of the disease, dengue haemorrhagic fever with associated shock,
said health officials.
--
