[6] Malaysia (Negeri Sembilan)
Date: 13 Oct 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The Star 10 Oct 2003 [edited]
<http://www.thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2003/10/10/nation/6458603&sec=nation>

Dengue outbreak in 4 areas
-----------------------------------
4 housing estates [in Seremban] have been declared as dengue outbreak areas
by the state Health Department yesterday. They are Taman Paroi Jaya,
Panchor Jaya, Taman Tuanku Jaafar, and Taman Rasah Jaya.
State health director Dr Rosnah Ismail said the outbreak had reached an
alarming stage and the department had taken precautionary measures. She
said 1439 cases were recorded since January 2003 to 4 Oct 2003, and 72 were
haemorrhagic. Dr Rosnah said the highest number of cases were reported in
Seremban (1124), Port Dickson (140) and Jempol (62).
